{"body": "Using multiple_of? for evaluating more than 1 variable using the existing method is completely wrong. We feel that when more than one variable has to be used, then we have to use an array as most of the times they are dynamic information rather than static. which means i could test 30 with 2,3,5 or 3,5  we or just 5 however these would have to be added as an array which means \r\n\r\n multiple_of?(*numbers) will fail if the numbers are passed as a dynamic array.\r\n\r\n-- Satish N Kota & Manoj", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1213944", "created_at": "2011-05-21T08:51:30Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/1166#issuecomment-1213944", "updated_at": "2011-05-21T08:51:30Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 1166, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/heurion/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/heurion/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/heurion/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/heurion", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/heurion/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/heurion", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/heurion/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/1d6f5ce9301f003924204d0895b29a36?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Ffefa324999c170bdbbe766c0db6beb1d.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/heurion/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/heurion/received_events", "gravatar_id": "1d6f5ce9301f003924204d0895b29a36", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/heurion/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "heurion", "type": "User", "id": 374397, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/heurion/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52385c6dbd3543c151011eee"}, "id": 1213944, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/1166"}
